Become a Member
/.section-header
By becoming a member of the Boca Raton Historical Society, you become our partner in the building of your community and keeping "
History Alive

Our Membership Program provides different levels with exciting benefits

Unlimited free admission to The Schmidt Boca Raton History Museum
Complimentary or reduced admission to programs, events, lectures, and tours
Discount at the History Museum Store
Name listed in the donor foyer (select levels)
Receive a one-year
Boca
magazine subscription (select levels)

/.page-hero
Who We Are
/.page-hero__title
/.page-hero__header
/.page-hero
Home
About
Who We Are
The Boca Raton Historical Society
Your browser doesn't support video.
Please download the file:
video/mp4
The BRHS was founded in 1972 as a private, non-profit member organization and is headquartered in Historic Town Hall, built in 1927 and listed on the National Register of Historic Places.
The BRHS owns and operates The Schmidt Boca Raton History Museum, which opened in November 2021 after extensive building upgrades and the installation of its
History Alive!
exhibits.
The mission and purpose of the Boca Raton Historical Society is to collect, preserve, and present information and artifacts relevant to the past and evolving history of Boca Raton and to maintain a visible role in education and advocacy of historic preservation in our community.
